headline: Here's the Average Net Worth by Age and 5 Ways to Make Money in 2025 and Beyond
summary: The Federal Reserve conducts its Survey of Consumer Finances (SCF) every three years.  The report provides a snapshot of the financial conditions of U.S. households, measuring income, assets, and debt across various demographic categories.  The median net worth among U.S. families at the time was $192,700.
